@startuml
title Activity Diagram: Handle Completion / Failure

' Text Description:
' 1. The system identifies a signal indicating the workflow should end.
' 2. The system checks if the termination was caused by a runtime error.
' 3. If an error exists, the system logs the details and sets the status to FAILED.
' 4. If no error, the system captures final outputs and sets the status to COMPLETED.
' 5. The system archives the full execution history and notifies the actor.

start
:Identify termination signal;
if (Error detected?) then (yes)
  :Log error and set status to FAILED;
else (no)
  :Capture output and set status to COMPLETED;
endif
:Archive Execution History;
:Notify System Actor;
stop
@enduml